<h2>Sidebar General</h2>
<p>
The sidebar, also known as the menu, is a narrow vertical column often jam-packed with lots of information about a website. Found on most WordPress sites, the sidebar is usually placed on the right or left-hand side of the web page, though in some cases, a site will feature two sidebars, one on each side of the main content where your posts are found. This tutorial examines some of the information items and features generally found in the sidebar. After reading this article you'll feel more comfortable in adding or changing the content of your own sidebar. <br/>
In Striking, wo set several default sidebar, you can find them in the right sider of the <a href="<?php echo get_option('siteurl'); ?>/wp-admin//widgets.php">Appearance->Wigets</a> page.
</p>
<h2>Edit Sidebar</h2>
<p>If you want to edit the sidebar which be found already, follow the step below:
	<ol>
		<li>Go to <a href="<?php echo get_option('siteurl'); ?>/wp-admin//widgets.php">Appearance->Wigets</a>.</li>
		<li>Locate the sidebar you want to edit, click the dropdown of it on.</li>
		<li>Drag widgets you want to use from the middle to the sidebar to activate them. The wigits are in the <strong>Available Widgets</strong> module and <strong>Inactive Widgets  Widgets	</strong> module. </li>
		<li>Edit the wigits in the sidebar dropdown, then save it.</li>
		<li>You can also remove the wigits from sidebar. Drag widget you want to remove out off the sidebar. IF you want to deactivate them and delete their settings, you can drop it to <strong>Available Widgets</strong>, or you may drop it to <strong>Inactive Widgets</strong>to keep their setting by drop it to </li>
	</ol>
</p>
<h2>Add Custom Siderbar</h2>
<p>In striking, wo provide the function of add custom sidebar. You can go to <a href="<?php echo get_option('siteurl'); ?>/wp-admin/admin.php?page=theme_sidebar">Strinking->Homepage</a>.Enter the name of sidebar you want to create. Then click <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. At last you may find the sidebar you creat in he right sider of the <a href="<?php echo get_option('siteurl'); ?>/wp-admin//widgets.php">Appearance->Wigets</a> page. You can edit it as usual.
</p>